<BLOCKQUOTE>Posted by
Llabak of COR on 12:15:23 9/3/1999 from 129.79.123.245:<p>
In reply to: <a href="http://cor.simplenet.com/Mage/mageboard.mv?parm_func=showmsg+parm_msgnum=1000160">Can we use all the things we summon?</a> posted by 
Diarmuid on 6:42:19 9/2/1999 from 130.110.2.242:<p>
Hi diarmuid.<br><br>First, yes we can use all our summoned weapons.  I believe that all the summoned weapons use the piercing skill.  So you can use the summoned sword, but you don't need 1hs for it.  And of course, you can use the summoned spear as well.  I bought myself a runed totem pretty early in life, though, so I never bothered to buy any of the summon wepons spells.<br><br>As far as the gate spell, While I don't know the specific location, what you will usually find in spellcaster guild areas is that there is one merchant who sells all the spells common to the 4 classes.  So there'll be one merchant in the common area that sells, gate, bind, some of the shielding spells, and some others.  In felwithe, this person should probably be before you go through the teleporter to the actual mage guild.<br><br>Hopes this helps.<br><br>Yours for the Good<br>Llabak
</MvEVAL>
